    {
      "id": "62dac710-5d40-4faf-9598-912a9e6a9981",
      "name": "Cosmo 250D",
      "brand": "FILMRISS",
      "iso": 250,
      "format": "35mm",
      "type": "Color Negative",
      "expiration_date": "2027-01-01",
      "created_at": "2025-08-22T07:08:45.21",
      "user_id": "335461ec-7719-4c39-b023-c600e11d308c",
      "count": 2,
      "notes": "Cosmo 250D is a respooled cinema film based on Kodak Vision3 250D—a material used worldwide in professional film productions and known for its natural color reproduction. Originally intended for the big screen, we now make this daylight film available for your 35mm camera.\n\nWith its medium sensitivity (ISO 250, adjusted for daylight), it delivers finely graded colors and a very pleasing, subtle grain. Even with high-contrast subjects such as bright sunlight or colorful scenes, the look remains harmonious and balanced. Skin tones appear particularly realistic, while rich colors and clear details are preserved.\n\n\nISO\nECN-2: ISO 250 (we recommend ISO 200 for better results)\n\nC-41: ISO 400 (we recommend ISO 250 for better results)\n\n \n\nDX code\n\nTo reduce costs and operate more sustainably, we recycle old film cartridges. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the correct DX code.\n\n \n\nRemjet\n\nThis film doesn't have a Remjet coating, but rather the new Kodak AHU coating, and can therefore be developed in any photo lab using standard C-41 chemistry. Developing in ECN-2 is, of course, still possible.",
      "price": 4.99,
      "updated_at": "2025-08-22T07:10:26.734106+00:00",
      "is_bulk_film": false,
      "bulk_length_meters": null,
      "bulk_quantity": null,
