      "user_id": "335461ec-7719-4c39-b023-c600e11d308c",
      "count": 2,
      "notes": "Cosmo 500T is a respooled cinema film based on Kodak Vision3 500T—a material used worldwide in professional film productions and known for its natural color reproduction. Originally intended for the big screen, we now make this daylight film available for your 35mm camera.\n\nWith its medium sensitivity (ISO 500, adjusted for artificial light), it delivers finely graded colors and a very pleasing, subtle grain. Even with high-contrast subjects such as bright sunlight or colorful scenes, the look remains harmonious and balanced. Skin tones appear particularly realistic, while rich colors and clear details are preserved.\n\n\nISO\nECN-2: ISO 500 (we recommend ISO 400 for better results)\n\nC-41: ISO 800 (we recommend ISO 500 for better results)\n\n \n\nDX code\n\nTo reduce costs and operate more sustainably, we recycle old film cartridges. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the correct DX code.\n\n \n\nRemjet\n\nThis film doesn't have a Remjet coating, but rather the new Kodak AHU coating, and can therefore be developed in any photo lab using standard C-41 chemistry. Developing in ECN-2 is, of course, still possible.",
      "price": 4.99,
      "updated_at": "2025-08-22T07:11:18.596+00:00",
